b'{"data_headers":{"result_code":1},"data":{"information":{"article_id":1386,"category_name":"Updates","pr_category_id":"2","title_name":"Version Update [Update]","message":"<div><span style=\\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\\"><strong>[Addendum <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1593054000\\"><\/span>]<\/strong><\/span><br>As a token of our appreciation, the following item has been sent to players who started playing before <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1593054000\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br>\\u30fbTenfold Summon Voucher x1<\/div><div><br>This gift can be claimed from your goodie box for up to seven days after reception. If the gift isn&#39;t retrieved within seven days, it will be lost.<\/div><div><br>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.<\/div><hr><div><span style=\\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\\"><strong>[Addendum <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1592546400\\"><\/span>]<\/strong><\/span><\/div><div>\\u25a0Other Changes<\/div><div>We will remove the text about resetting Skill Shift from the details of skills with the Skill Shift feature.<br>Note: This change only affects the descriptive text. The conditions for resetting Skill Shift will not change. For information about resetting Skill Shift, select Help, then select Special Effects and see the About Resetting section under Skill Shift.<\/div><div>This change will be applied in a data update around <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1593754200\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br>\\u25a0Issues Fixed<\/div><div>\\u30fbWhen the adventurer Victor&#39;s Steel Formation skill is in Skill Shift Phase II, damage dealt to enemies who are afflicted with burn is increased.<br>\\u30fbIf the adventurer Linnea&#39;s force strike charge level is level one or higher and she uses her upgraded force strike immediately before it finishes charging while Cluster Amaryllis is active due to her Bliss Eternal skill, then Cluster Amaryllis will not end.<\/div><hr><div>Version 1.21.0 will be available for download around <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1592971200\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>You may install it when it becomes available; otherwise, an automatic update will occur at approximately <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1593054000\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>When you update to version 1.21.0 and play co-op, you will no longer be matched with players using earlier versions of the game. Rooms created by players playing earlier versions will not display in the Room List, and you will not be able to join them using Find a Room, Join Nearby Players, Enter an ID, or alliance chat.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>To celebrate the update, we&#39;ll be sending all players a Tenfold Summon Voucher after the automatic update.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>This notice will be modified after it has been distributed.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Note: The Tenfold Summon Voucher will not be distributed until after the automatic update, even if you complete the update to version 1.21.0 early.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Update Details<\/div><div>\\u30fbIncreased team slots<\/div><div>We will add groups of teams that you can switch between. The number of teams in a single group will be reduced from nine to six, but there will be nine groups of teams in total. With this change, you will now be able to build a total of 54 teams.<\/div><div>Note: In regard to teams built before version 1.21.0, teams in slots one through six will become the first group of teams, and the remaining three, teams seven through nine, will be registered to the second group of teams.<\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/1dae0f78956d2fa3bfd8bc06b2ce29e4.png\\"><\/div><div>Additionally, you will be able to register a name for each team. Other players will be unable to see your team names.<\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/1299708f5d48e56822d6251c474f428e.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbAdditional display option for the Dragon&#39;s Roost<\/div><div>You will be able to switch to a 2D version of the Dragon&#39;s Roost from the System tab under Options in the Menu.<\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/6e17641a482475080fef88873cf933d3.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbObtain 3\\u2605 adventurers when starting the game<\/div><div>Note: This feature will be applied starting <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1593410400\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div>When starting the game from the beginning, players will automatically receive 3\\u2605 adventurers during the tutorial. Additionally, teams comprised of 3\\u2605 adventurers will be set by default when building teams.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Along with the above change, players who completed the applicable tutorial before <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1593410400\\"><\/span> will receive the eligible 3\\u2605 adventurers as a gift. Players who have already obtained the eligible 3\\u2605 adventurers will instead receive 150 eldwater per 3\\u2605 adventurer.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Finally, the 3\\u2605 adventurers who can be obtained when starting the game will no longer appear in future summon showcases starting <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1593410400\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>The 3\\u2605 adventurers who will no longer appear in summon showcases are as follows.<\/div><div>Aoi (flame\/blade)<\/div><div>Joe (flame\/bow)<\/div><div>Aurien (flame\/staff)<\/div><div>Zardin (water\/sword)<\/div><div>Jurota (water\/blade)<\/div><div>Waike (water\/bow)<\/div><div>Ricardt (water\/staff)<\/div><div>Melody (wind\/blade)<\/div><div>Francesca (wind\/dagger)<\/div><div>Nicolas (wind\/wand)<\/div><div>Sophie (wind\/staff)<\/div><div>Irfan (light\/dagger)<\/div><div>Linus (light\/axe)<\/div><div>Malka (light\/lance)<\/div><div>Hope (light\/staff)<\/div><div>Vida (shadow\/dagger)<\/div><div>Erik (shadow\/axe)<\/div><div>Zace (shadow\/lance)<\/div><div>Althemia (shadow\/wand)<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbNew feature for deleting quest and story data<\/div><div>From the System tab under Options in the Menu, you will be able to delete quest and story data for all cleared quests in the main campaign, or simply delete all quest and story data. By deleting quest and story data you can reduce how much storage Dragalia Lost uses, but if you play a quest or story again after deleting data, then you will need to redownload the data.<\/div><div>Note: Deleting quest or story data will not change your clear status for the quest or the completion status for endeavors. Some quest and story data cannot be deleted. After deleting quest and story data, you will be returned to the Home screen.<\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/c2a30dd676c34ad26ade975acbc8478f.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbIncreased capacity for weapons, wyrmprints, and dragons<\/div><div>The capacity for weapons, wyrmprints, and dragons at the start of the game will be increased as follows.<\/div><div>Weapons: +100<\/div><div>Wyrmprints: +100<\/div><div>Dragons: +50<\/div><div>This change will be applied in a data update around <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1592978400\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div>Note: For players who have already started playing the game, each capacity will be increased as described above, regardless of how much their capacity has already been expanded.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Other Changes<\/div><div>\\u30fbReductions to the space required for 2D data<\/div><div>As part of the effort to reduce space requirements, we will change the compression format for some 2D data. Due to this, the appearance of certain images may change in some places. With this change, a large data download will occur on the title screen the first time you start the game after updating to version 1.21.0. We ask for your understanding, as this change will help reduce the space requirements for the application.<\/div><div>Note: We recommend downloading this data while connected to Wi-Fi.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWe will add an option to the data download selection when starting the game which will only download the bare minimum amount of data required to clear main campaign chapter 1 \/ 1-1, In Pursuit of the Shard.<\/div><div>\\u30fbIf data will be deleted during a data update, the amount of data to be deleted will be displayed in the data download pop-up.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWhen a new summon showcase starts, the First Encounters for certain new adventurers will automatically play.<\/div><div>\\u30fbStarting around <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1592978400\\"><\/span>, Expert difficulty will be available at all times for all Elemental Ruins quests.<\/div><div>\\u30fbStarting around <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1592978400\\"><\/span>, the maximum level for Dracolith facilities will be increased to level 30.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWe will change the name for the Recovery Potency +X% buff to Recovery +X%. Along with this change, the skill description text for some adventurers and weapons will be adjusted.<br>\\u3000Note: This change only affects the notation. The effect itself will not change. This change will be applied in a data update around <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1592803800\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWe will also adjust the UI on some screens.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Balance Adjustments<\/div><div>\\u30fbWe will remove the first part of certain quests in chapters one through 13 of the main campaign on Normal difficulty.<\/div><div>Note: We will not alter the quests or stories for the Hard and Very Hard difficulty levels.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWe have adjusted the timing at which the adventurer Yurius ends his dragondrive when participating in a battle as an AI adventurer.<\/div><div>\\u30fbAs part of an issue that was addressed, the following balance adjustment has been made to Volk&#39;s Wrath.<br>When a helper skill is used at the same time that Volk uses Ravenous Claws while in human form, the controlled adventurer will now be selected as a target for Ravenous Claws as intended.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Issues Fixed<\/div><div>\\u30fbWhen the display method for the Craft tab under Crafting was set to Max Tier List, the skill for tier II Agito weapons displayed as the skill for tier I Agito weapons.<\/div><div>\\u30fbIn the Royal Regimen, there were some cases where an endeavor completion notice was received when clearing the endeavor&#39;s conditions even though it was not unlocked yet.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWhen using Heinwald&#39;s Call of Chaos skill as a shared skill, the amount of recovered HP was lower than expected.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe effects of abilities such as Skill Damage +X% or Energized aren&#39;t applied to the damage dealt when the Burning Ambition buff from Nobunaga&#39;s Dream Offensive skill ends.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Notes:<\/div><div>1. It may take time for the store to reflect the updated information. Players may not be able to perform updates due to their device&#39;s data cache being full. If you are unable to perform the update, restart your device, and then try downloading it from the store.<\/div><div>2. Any adventurers and game screenshots shown are still in development.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.<\/div>","start_time":1592373600,"prev_article_id":"1325","next_article_id":"1433","image_path":"","update_time":1593054089}}}'